In this speech delivered by LTG H.R. McMaster on December 12, 2017, he discusses the importance of the Anglo-American alliance in promoting peace and stability in the world. He emphasizes the need to adapt to the emerging strategic environment to protect core interests and addresses four national security priorities: defending against threats from revisionist powers (China and Russia), rogue regimes (Iran and North Korea), and transnational terrorist organizations; advancing economic prosperity; promoting peace through strength; and advancing American influence. McMaster also highlights the importance of the United States and the United Kingdom working together to address common threats and seize shared opportunities.